From 8c9c1eb50c395bd81d1d711fb643cacd712c0a6e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:17:50 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 02/10] feat[core/lang]: add query::tokenize() and
 query::validate()

First two public APIs of the sen::lang::query namespace, built on top of
the Stage 1 tolerant scanner and recoverable parser.

- tokenize(text) returns a list of typed tokens (keyword, string,
  number, operator, identifier, comment, error) with spans, suitable
  for syntax highlighting. Runs on the same scanner as
  validate/complete/guideAt so consumers share a single source of
  truth.
- validate(text, types, buses) returns a DiagnosticList. Errors cover
  syntax, property missing on a known class, and literal-vs-property
  type mismatch. Infos cover class not yet in the type registry and
  session/bus not yet discovered; these auto-clear once the thing
  shows up.

BusLookup is a struct of std::function<...>s rather than a virtual
interface so callers can bind any source of session/bus information.
